# Next.js App Router + Tailwind + SEO

Specialize in TypeScript for Next.js App Router apps using Tailwind CSS. Read `node_modules/next/dist/docs/` when APIs may differ from training data.

## Key Requirements

1. Place routes/components under `src/app` using App Router conventions.
2. Server Components by default; Client Components only for interactivity or client state.
3. Modern TypeScript: functional components, proper typing at boundaries.
4. Responsive layouts via Tailwind utilities.
5. Modular, reusable components aligned to design sections.
6. Fetch on the server with `fetch` + caching/revalidation when appropriate.
7. Use the Metadata API for SEO (`export const metadata` / `generateMetadata`).
8. Use `next/image` for optimized images.
9. Prefer semantic HTML and ARIA for accessibility.
10. Use `error.tsx` / `global-error.tsx` and `loading.tsx` where useful.
11. API routes as `route.ts` handlers under `src/app/api`.
12. Choose static or dynamic rendering intentionally (SSG/SSR/ISR patterns).

## Code Patterns

```tsx
// Client only when needed
'use client'

interface ComponentNameProps {
  title: string
}

export const ComponentName = ({ title }: ComponentNameProps) => {
  return <h1>{title}</h1>
}
```

```tsx
// Page: default export; server fetch example
async function getData() {
  const res = await fetch('https://api.example.com/data', {
    next: { revalidate: 3600 },
  })
  if (!res.ok) throw new Error('Failed to fetch data')
  return res.json()
}

export default async function Page() {
  const data = await getData()
  return <main>{/* render */}</main>
}
```

```tsx
import type { Metadata } from 'next'

export const metadata: Metadata = {
  title: 'Page Title',
  description: 'Page description',
}
```

## Guidelines

- TypeScript only; Tailwind for styling (avoid inline styles).
- Named exports for reusable components; default export for pages.
- Avoid redundant annotations; prefer inference and `React.ReactNode` only when needed.
- Environment config via Next.js env conventions.
- Parallelize independent data fetching; document forced sequential awaits.
- Keep components accessible (WCAG-minded structure and labels).
